Scope
------------
> reduce risks
> benfit
> what will provide value
> way of connection (VPN, Plug into network)
Discovery
------------
> Physical Access
  > Physical Security
  > OSINT
    > passive gathering
  > Social Engineering
> Sniffing
  > passive Recon
    > tcpdump
      > Email, Websites, [...]
  > watch network trafic
    > MAC Addresses
> ARP
  > resolve IP Addresses
  > ARP table
> ICMP
  > Traceroute
  > Ping
    > dropped packets
    > Typ 8 - echo Request
    > Typ 0 - echo Reply
    
> Tools
  > Wireshark
    > select interfaces
    > IP is at MAC
    > Statistics - Endpoints
  > ARP-Scan
    > sudo arp-scan -I <Interface> -g <local IP>/<CIDR>
  > Ping
    > ping <IP>
    > packets transmitted, received, packet loss, Error Message
  > fping
    > fping -I <Interface> -g <local IP>/<CIDR> -a (everything alive)
    > stderr 2 to /dev/null (2>/dev/null)
  > nmap
    > -sn (Ping Sweep Scan) <IP>/<CIDR>
  > zenmap (GUI Version of nmap)
    > Target like nmap (<IP>/<CIDR>)
    > Profile Ping Scan
   
